Thirteen-year-old JC van Loggerenberg was found on the tracks near the Witpoortjie station on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - Metrorail says its investigating the cause of an accident that left a teenage boy dead after he fell from a moving train.Thirteen-year-old JC van Loggerenberg was found on the tracks near the Witpoortjie station on Wednesday.It s understood he was on his way to collect his report.Metrorail s Lillian Mofokeng says they re trying to establish how the boy ended up outside the train. It s not like it was an overcrowded train because at the time the incident happened we know the kind of service we were operating and it was not a case of an overcrowded train at all. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)